{"type":"message","id":"76d0a769","parentId":"545153e6","timestamp":"2026-03-29T15:30:58.902Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a pre-compaction memory flush turn. I need to check if there's anything worth remembering from today's session and append it to memory/2026-03-.md if that file exists, or create it if needed.\n\nLet me think about what happened today:\n1. MX deploy commands were executed multiple times successfully\n2. User wanted to process a MingoX article from a Feishu document link\n3. I tried multiple approaches to get the Feishu document content but couldn't access it directly\n4. User provided an image of the document content\n5. I successfully extracted the text from the image using the image tool\n6. I generated a new article about \"AI创作黄金10条\" based on the extracted content\n7. The article was created, homepage updated, committed to Git, pushed to Gitee, and deployed to EdgeOne\n8. User later sent the actual text content of the original article they wanted (关于老年人AI教育的研究报告)\n\nKey things to remember:\n- Feishu documents cannot be directly accessed via web fetch due to permissions\n- Image recognition can be used as a fallback when document links don't work\n- MX workflow: pull → process → commit → push → deploy\n- The user's preferred workflow and content generation patterns\n\nLet me check if the memory file exists first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d3a38416a581374e59c4aee397f8f","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/workspace/projects/workspace/memory/2026-03-29.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"coze","model":"auto","usage":{"input":40270,"output":570,"cacheRead":34176,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75016,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774798250441}}
