{"type":"message","id":"17f8484b","parentId":"f0f9712d","timestamp":"2026-03-29T15:52:47.422Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"完成了！现在让我总结一下修正内容。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## ✅ 两篇文章已完全修正并重新部署！\n\n### 🔄 修正内容对照\n\n| 修正项 | 修正前 | 修正后 |\n|--------|--------|--------|\n| **英文导语** | ❌ 无 | ✅ 每篇第一段英文导语 |\n| **词汇密度** | ⚠️ 每段1处 | ✅ 符合每1-2句1处要求 |\n| **用词水平** | ⚠️ 高中常见词 | ✅ 考研级别词汇 |\n| **相邻检查** | ✅ 无相邻 | ✅ 无相邻 |\n\n### 📝 第一篇：AI创作黄金10条\n\n**标题:** 📝 AI创作黄金10条 | AI Creation Golden Rules: 10 Ways to Stand Out\n\n**英文导语:**\n```\nIn the AI creation era, how to make your content standout? \nThese 10 golden rules help you craft viral content!\n```\n\n**词汇标注:** 6个核心词汇（考研级）\n- standout (杰出，脱颖而出)\n- audience (受众，目标群体)\n- resonate (共鸣)\n- temperature (温度，情感温度)\n- competitiveness (竞争力)\n- credibility (可信度)\n\n### 📝 第二篇：老年人AI学习需求研究\n\n**标题:** 👵 老年人AI学习需求研究 | Study on Elderly AI Learning Needs: 6 Types & Standards\n\n**英文导语:**\n```\nBased on 500 hours of in-depth interviews, this study \nidentifies six types of elderly AI learners. Over half \nof respondents' learning motivations are deeply interwoven \nwith capability enhancement and value monetization.\n```\n\n**词汇标注:** 13个核心词汇（考研级）\n- identifies (识别，梳理出)\n- motivations (动机，动力)\n- interwoven (交织)\n- monetization (变现)\n- germinal (萌芽的)\n- prompt (提示词)\n- imperative (必需品，刚需)\n- fulfill (实现，圆梦)\n- suspended (悬置的)\n- axiomatic (不证自明的，理所当然的)\n- exclusion (排斥)\n- stratified (分层的)\n- endogenous (内生的)\n\n---\n\n### 🌐 访问链接\n\n**EdgeOne Pages（有效链接）：**\n```\nhttps://mingox-dzlbtybw.edgeone.cool?eo_token=13335d4910042813090c65ab32500a44&eo_time=1774799557\n```\n\n---\n\n**现在两篇文章完全符合 README.md 的格式规范了！** ✅\n\n包括：\n- ✅ 英文导语段落\n- ✅ 考研级词汇\n- ✅ 符合密度要求\n- ✅ 完整词汇表（含音标）"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"coze","model":"auto","usage":{"input":914,"output":616,"cacheRead":118848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120378,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"to